look I was going for.

13:53.280 --> 13:55.880
RITA WEST: Excuse
us for a minute.

13:56.000 --> 13:57.160
I thought you were
doing a job, not

13:57.280 --> 13:58.560
picking up waifs and strays.

13:58.680 --> 14:01.200
Yeah, there was a
bit of a hitch in that.

14:01.320 --> 14:02.680
He's got nowhere else to go.

14:02.800 --> 14:03.560
Jesus, Ted.

14:03.680 --> 14:04.800
You're such a softy.

14:04.920 --> 14:06.040
Me?

14:06.160 --> 14:07.720
What the hell was
going on with Carol?

14:07.840 --> 14:09.320
She just needs
a bit of time out.

14:09.440 --> 14:12.960
You don't get between
a man and his wife.

14:13.080 --> 14:14.400
[car approaches]

14:14.520 --> 14:17.320
[tires screech]

14:20.640 --> 14:22.080
Lefty says you
got my wife here.

14:22.200 --> 14:24.720
I do, as a matter of fact.

14:24.840 --> 14:25.960
Carol!

14:26.080 --> 14:27.640
Carol, get your
bloody ass out here!

14:27.760 --> 14:29.760
Hey, mate, why don't you comeinside, have a chat about it?

14:29.880 --> 14:30.640
Carol!

14:34.760 --> 14:36.120
Get in the car.

14:36.240 --> 14:37.000
No.

14:39.920 --> 14:41.160
Get in the bloody car.

14:41.280 --> 14:43.080
I'm not going to,
and you can't make me.

14:43.200 --> 14:44.440
We'll see about that.

14:44.560 --> 14:45.920
I'm not coming home.

14:46.040 --> 14:46.880
What?

14:47.000 --> 14:48.360
I'm leaving you, you idiot.

14:48.480 --> 14:49.680
And I never want
to see you again.

14:49.800 --> 14:51.320
So there.

14:51.440 --> 14:53.200
You walk out on me, and youwon't see another bloody penny!

14:53.320 --> 14:54.760
I don't see a
bloody penny anyway,

14:54.880 --> 14:56.560
and I pay for the groceries.

14:56.680 --> 14:59.040
You're a tight bastard who onlycares about his stupid mamie.

14:59.160 --> 15:00.640
[ANGRILY] Don't you
talk about my mamie!

15:00.760 --> 15:03.320
Bugger her and her bloodyrosary, and her stupid saints.

15:09.040 --> 15:09.840
Inside now.

15:09.960 --> 15:10.720
I was making a stand.

15:10.840 --> 15:12.160
Inside now.

15:12.280 --> 15:13.600
Come on, Phineas.Let's take it somewhere else.

15:13.720 --> 15:14.480
Hey, hey, hey!

15:14.600 --> 15:15.720
Come on.

15:15.840 --> 15:16.960
Come on, let's go
somewhere else, OK?

15:20.200 --> 15:21.600
It's your bloody wife
putting ideas in her.

15:21.720 --> 15:23.120
Carol can think for herself.

15:23.240 --> 15:24.560
Sometimes.

15:24.680 --> 15:26.040
Surely you two
can work this out.

15:26.160 --> 15:27.320
No, she's done.

15:27.440 --> 15:28.520
She's done [inaudible].

15:28.640 --> 15:30.640
Maybe if your mom went home.

15:30.760 --> 15:32.480
PHINEAS O'DRISCOLL: What areyou saying about my mamie?

15:32.600 --> 15:33.480
Nothing.

15:33.600 --> 15:34.920
Nothing at all.

15:35.040 --> 15:37.240
So when are we
going to do this job?

15:37.360 --> 15:39.400
It's just Talita
wants another day.

15:39.520 --> 15:40.400
Talita?

15:40.520 --> 15:41.760
She's a babe.

15:41.880 --> 15:43.360
Yeah, well, you're
welcome to her.

15:43.480 --> 15:46.000
How could that happen
when she's keen on you?

15:46.120 --> 15:48.480
We can't have another crackat the job until next Thursday.

15:48.600 --> 15:50.000
Why?

15:50.120 --> 15:51.200
Because that's the daythey bring the payroll, Bert.

15:51.320 --> 15:52.120
Hey, that's right.

15:52.240 --> 15:53.800
[inaudible]

15:53.920 --> 15:55.120
You don't want to do that.

15:55.240 --> 15:56.880
We were married
in the sight of God.

15:57.000 --> 15:57.800
She can't walk out on me.

15:57.920 --> 15:59.040
Give her some space.

15:59.160 --> 16:01.240
Don't tell me what to do.

16:01.360 --> 16:03.240
You and your wife actingall high and bloody mighty.

16:03.360 --> 16:04.480
Well, you can bloody--
- Come on, mate.

16:04.600 --> 16:05.440
Nah.

16:05.560 --> 16:06.760
You can stick the lot of it.

16:06.880 --> 16:08.720
While she's at your
bloody house, I'm out.

16:08.840 --> 16:10.560
Out of what?

16:10.680 --> 16:12.480
The game.

16:12.600 --> 16:13.800
I've had it.

16:13.920 --> 16:17.360
[breathing heavily]
I've had it up to here!

16:17.480 --> 16:20.000
Just what we needed.

16:20.120 --> 16:22.440
[grunts and groans]

16:24.520 --> 16:27.320
[disco music plays]

16:27.440 --> 16:29.320
[laughs]

16:29.440 --> 16:30.240
Woo!

16:30.360 --> 16:31.120
Ow!

16:31.240 --> 16:32.160
Shake that booty!

16:32.280 --> 16:33.160
Woo-oo!

16:33.280 --> 16:34.600
Come on, Wolfie, don't be shy.

16:34.720 --> 16:36.480
I'm not dancing the disco.

16:36.600 --> 16:37.440
Aw.

16:37.560 --> 16:40.400
Music for your soul, man.

16:40.520 --> 16:41.360
Hi, Ted.

16:41.480 --> 16:42.840
How are ya?

16:42.960 --> 16:44.320
Been better.

16:44.440 --> 16:46.720
Falani's showing Carolhow to do the Samoan hustle.

16:46.840 --> 16:47.960
Is he now?

16:48.080 --> 16:50.320
I haven't had this
much fun in years.

16:50.440 --> 16:51.760
OK.

16:51.880 --> 16:53.600
might be time to
wrap up this party.

16:53.720 --> 16:55.320
Your room's down
the end of the hall.

16:55.440 --> 16:56.880
Your bed's made up.

16:57.000 --> 16:59.280
Bless you, Mrs. West, forinviting me into your home,

16:59.400 --> 17:02.080
for your lovely food, andpity for the homeless.

17:02.200 --> 17:02.960
My pleasure.

17:03.080 --> 17:04.080
Whoops.

17:04.200 --> 17:05.960
Ooh, lean on me,
Mrs. O'Driscoll.

17:06.080 --> 17:07.240
Call me Carol.

17:07.360 --> 17:08.600
Lean on me, Mrs. Carol.

17:08.720 --> 17:09.560
CAROL O'DRISCOLL: [laughs]

17:09.680 --> 17:11.400
[laughs]

17:11.520 --> 17:13.040
That guy is weird.

17:13.160 --> 17:16.000
RITA WEST: He has very nicemanners, and he did the dishes.

17:16.120 --> 17:16.920
Disco sucks.

17:19.920 --> 17:22.000
How long's Carol
going to be staying?

17:22.120 --> 17:23.840
As long as she wants to be.

17:23.960 --> 17:26.240
Phineas says he's quittingthe gang on account of it.

17:26.360 --> 17:28.040
Oh, how terrible.

17:28.160 --> 17:29.120
It's not great, Rita.

17:29.240 --> 17:32.520
I really don't want to argue.

17:32.640 --> 17:34.400
How long is that boy
going to be staying?

17:34.520 --> 17:35.920
Thought you didn't
want to argue.

17:36.040 --> 17:37.880
You know how I feel aboutmen who beat up on women.

17:38.000 --> 17:40.680
Yeah, and I'm not a fan ofMuldoon and his bully boys.

17:40.800 --> 17:44.160
Well, we both
have our principles,

17:44.280 --> 17:48.240
and that makes us
quits, doesn't it?

17:48.360 --> 17:50.000
Where are you going
to on this fine day?

17:50.120 --> 17:51.480
School.

17:51.600 --> 17:53.240
Ah, I don't do school.

17:53.360 --> 17:56.800
I do my living on the streetsand the university of life.

17:56.920 --> 17:58.600
Like disco dancing?

17:58.720 --> 18:00.680
I also know martial arts--

18:00.800 --> 18:01.920
how to please the lady.

18:02.040 --> 18:04.080
[chuckles] Oh, yeah.

18:04.200 --> 18:06.080
And I can see into the future.

18:06.200 --> 18:09.080
Eh, I bet you $2
that in 10 minutes,

18:09.200 --> 18:10.760
I'll be driving a
kickass [inaudible]..

18:10.880 --> 18:11.640
Bullshit.

18:18.640 --> 18:21.440
[engine starts]

18:22.600 --> 18:23.400
$2.

18:27.440 --> 18:29.040
You got something for me, Ted?

18:29.160 --> 18:30.280
I want to report a crime.

18:30.400 --> 18:31.840
No, coming from
you, that is funny.

18:31.960 --> 18:35.080
It's the [inaudible].

18:35.200 --> 18:39.160
Now your lot are busting intohouses looking for overstayers.

18:39.280 --> 18:40.520
[inaudible] we're
not, thank, Christ.

18:40.640 --> 18:41.480
You're still a copper.

18:41.600 --> 18:42.520
And you know other coppers.

18:42.640 --> 18:44.240
What about it?

18:44.360 --> 18:45.880
Poor bastards
in South Auckland

18:46.000 --> 18:47.480
have the cops taking them way.

18:47.600 --> 18:49.400
Then buggers are coming inand stealing all their stuff.

18:49.520 --> 18:50.560
Tragedy.

18:50.680 --> 18:52.720
But what do you care?

18:52.840 --> 18:53.840
Young friend of
my acquaintance

18:53.960 --> 18:55.000
told me what was going on.

18:55.120 --> 18:56.640
Well, maybe he
should call the police.

18:56.760 --> 18:58.720
Then he'll get taken away.

18:58.840 --> 19:02.080
Look, I'm not a fan ofthese bloody raids any more

19:02.200 --> 19:03.520
than you are.

19:03.640 --> 19:05.760
It's Muldoon going totake the heat off himself.

19:05.880 --> 19:07.040
I don't love the
coconuts, but it's not

19:07.160 --> 19:08.480
like they buggered the economy.

19:08.600 --> 19:10.720
What the hell do youexpect me to do about it?

19:10.840 --> 19:12.920
Well, your mates in
South Auckland-- tell

19:13.040 --> 19:15.320
them to do their bloody job.

19:15.440 --> 19:18.760
That's the address of thehouse that got cleaned out.

19:18.880 --> 19:20.960
This is very community
minded of you, Ted.

19:21.080 --> 19:22.600
There's a line
between right and wrong.

19:22.720 --> 19:26.320
And speaking of lines, howdid you come to be down the line

19:26.440 --> 19:27.680
in South Auckland?

19:27.800 --> 19:28.600
Just passing through.

19:28.720 --> 19:30.480
We were going fishing.

19:30.600 --> 19:32.040
Sure, you were.

19:32.160 --> 19:33.560
It's a free country.

19:33.680 --> 19:34.960
Or it's meant to be.

19:35.080 --> 19:35.920
If you say so, Ted.

19:41.520 --> 19:44.160
- Hello, [inaudible].
- No.

19:44.280 --> 19:45.280
I have an appointment.

19:45.400 --> 19:46.400
I'm very sorry.

19:46.520 --> 19:48.120
But I am in no
fit state to work.

19:48.240 --> 19:49.400
Hmm.

19:49.520 --> 19:51.160
Yes, Lefty tells me
you've left Phineas.

19:51.280 --> 19:52.160
Yes.

19:52.280 --> 19:53.840
He's very upset, apparently.

19:53.960 --> 19:55.920
Passed out drunk
is what Ted told me.

19:56.040 --> 19:57.360
It's hard for men.

19:57.480 --> 19:59.240
They don't know how todeal with their feelings.

19:59.360 --> 20:02.320
You want me to
feel sorry for him?

20:02.440 --> 20:03.760
He's saying he'll
leave the gang.

20:03.880 --> 20:05.000
You want me to
get back with him

20:05.120 --> 20:06.320
because of the precious gang?

20:06.440 --> 20:08.640
I just think you
need to be practical.

20:08.760 --> 20:10.440
You know there's this
new law coming in.

20:10.560 --> 20:11.480
What law?

20:11.600 --> 20:13.160
The matrimonial
property thingy.

20:13.280 --> 20:15.160
If you wait a couple of months,then you can take him for all

20:15.280 --> 20:17.320
he's got, or half of it.

20:17.440 --> 20:19.120
I don't care.

20:19.240 --> 20:20.400
But it's not fair.

20:20.520 --> 20:22.880
In all these years,
and you get nothing.

20:23.000 --> 20:24.280
But I don't get nothing.

20:24.400 --> 20:26.720
I have my insurance.

20:26.840 --> 20:30.520
You mean the krugerrands?

20:30.640 --> 20:31.800
Sure.

20:31.920 --> 20:33.160
That was for when
our men weren't around.

20:33.280 --> 20:34.840
CAROL O'DRISCOLL: But I
don't have a man around.

20:34.960 --> 20:37.800
I'm going to buy myself acar, get some new clothes.

20:37.920 --> 20:41.320
Maybe I'll even take [inaudible]out on a date in my new car

20:41.440 --> 20:43.560
wearing my new clothes.

20:43.680 --> 20:46.960
Phineas can suck on that.

20:47.080 --> 20:48.080
See you at home.

20:48.200 --> 20:51.040
I'll get something for tea.

20:51.160 --> 20:54.120
That will be a worry.

20:54.240 --> 20:57.400
We have a bigger problemthan a burnt bloody dinner.

20:57.520 --> 20:58.400
Maybe.

20:58.520 --> 20:59.320
Forget maybe.

20:59.440 --> 21:00.800
You heard what she said.

21:00.920 --> 21:02.640
Carol's never been discreetat the best of times.

21:02.760 --> 21:04.000
She's all talk.

21:04.120 --> 21:07.080
If she starts shooting
her mouse off, fooling

21:07.200 --> 21:10.760
around the krugerrands, you knowyou and I are in serious shit.

21:15.840 --> 21:16.680
How was school?

21:16.800 --> 21:17.560
All right.

21:17.680 --> 21:19.440
What did you get, Falani?

21:19.560 --> 21:21.320
I had a quiet day--

21:21.440 --> 21:24.680
thinking of my family,
feeling sad for them.

21:24.800 --> 21:27.720
[tires squealing]

21:28.440 --> 21:29.080
Woo-hoo!

21:34.640 --> 21:36.480
If you wanted to callthem, that would be fine.

21:36.600 --> 21:39.080
Alas, they have
no phone in Samoa.

21:39.200 --> 21:40.080
Hello, everyone.

21:40.200 --> 21:42.160
I got the tea.

21:42.280 --> 21:45.480
Fried chicken-- this
is manna from heaven.

21:45.600 --> 21:46.720
I've been thinking
about cooking.

21:46.840 --> 21:48.000
And bugger it.

21:48.120 --> 21:49.760
From now on, I'm going
to buy everything.

21:49.880 --> 21:51.400
I like this plan.

21:51.520 --> 21:53.920
It's going to be takeawaysevery night, or I'm going out.

21:54.040 --> 21:54.960
Sounds expensive.

21:55.080 --> 21:56.840
I'm a woman of means.

21:56.960 --> 21:58.320
And this woman needs to party.

22:01.640 --> 22:02.760
Woman of means?

22:02.880 --> 22:03.960
What's she on about?

22:04.080 --> 22:05.480
She's got her sell on.

22:05.600 --> 22:06.960
If Phineas goes
out on his own,

22:07.080 --> 22:08.520
it could be bad for all of us.

22:08.640 --> 22:10.440
You know what he's likeafter he's had a few drinks.

22:10.560 --> 22:12.880
It's not a reason forhim to get back with Carol.

22:13.000 --> 22:15.560
And I've made up
my mind on this.

22:15.680 --> 22:17.520
[knocking]

22:17.640 --> 22:18.640
I don't want to [inaudible].

22:18.760 --> 22:20.120
But what?

22:20.240 --> 22:21.960
Only Carol's showing Falanihow to play strip poker.

22:22.080 --> 22:22.880
Who's winning?

22:23.000 --> 22:24.200
Falani.

22:24.320 --> 22:25.520
He's on his [inaudible].

22:30.600 --> 22:32.480
[disco music plays]

22:32.600 --> 22:35.560
You know, my
husband is a robber.

22:35.680 --> 22:37.160
You're kidding.

22:37.280 --> 22:42.280
They all rob all sorts ofthings-- jewelry stores, TAB.

22:42.400 --> 22:45.120
Falani, Carol's
a little bit drunk.

22:45.240 --> 22:46.280
Oh, no.

22:46.400 --> 22:47.400
That's terrible.

22:47.520 --> 22:48.880
And you should
really get to bed.

22:49.000 --> 22:50.360
OK.

22:50.480 --> 22:51.320
Good night.

22:51.440 --> 22:57.600
[inaudible]

22:57.720 --> 22:59.480
[turns music off]

22:59.600 --> 23:01.040
What the hell do you
think you're playing at?

23:01.160 --> 23:02.560
I was just having a
bit of fun, that's all.

23:02.680 --> 23:03.880
You know the rules.

23:04.000 --> 23:05.360
We don't talk about
what our husbands do.

23:05.480 --> 23:07.400
But he's not my
husband anymore.

23:07.520 --> 23:09.560
And leaving him was the
best thing I ever did.

23:13.200 --> 23:14.680
[music plays]

23:14.800 --> 23:16.920
VOCALISTS [SINGING]: And I'lltake you home on a bright

23:17.040 --> 23:23.800
and sunny morning We dancedall night until pale moonlight

23:23.920 --> 23:36.600
And now the day is dawning

23:36.720 --> 23:38.600
I think it might be a
good idea if Carol gets

23:38.720 --> 23:41.160
back together with Phineas.

23:41.280 --> 23:42.680
Thought you'd
made up your mind.

23:42.800 --> 23:44.440
I just wanted her to
stop being a doormat

23:44.560 --> 23:46.040
so Phineas would get
his act together.

23:46.160 --> 23:48.320
Well, you know
that's not very likely.

23:48.440 --> 23:50.880
Well, now, it's
fucking essential.

23:51.000 --> 23:52.200
And I need your help on this.

24:04.000 --> 24:05.880
Hey, Mrs. West.

24:06.000 --> 24:07.320
And Mrs. Carol.

24:07.440 --> 24:08.880
Hi.

24:09.000 --> 24:11.120
Oh, he's such a sweetie.

24:11.240 --> 24:12.200
Adorable.

24:12.320 --> 24:13.640
But we are off to work.

24:13.760 --> 24:14.680
See you, boys.

24:14.800 --> 24:16.000
Hey, Ted.

24:16.120 --> 24:17.480
Did you, by any chance,
hear from the police

24:17.600 --> 24:18.840
about the robbers?

24:18.960 --> 24:19.760
No, afraid not.

24:19.880 --> 24:21.600
I'll spot you later.

24:21.720 --> 24:24.480
[QUIETLY] Hey.

24:24.600 --> 24:26.800
Is your father
really a bank robber?

24:26.920 --> 24:27.800
Safe cracker.

24:27.920 --> 24:29.400
Cool.

24:29.520 --> 24:31.680
He's like Superman with
this double identity.

24:35.440 --> 24:36.840
Good day, Ted.

24:36.960 --> 24:38.000
Could I talk to you aboutyour mates down the line?

24:38.120 --> 24:39.280
About what?

24:39.400 --> 24:40.240
The robberies.

24:40.360 --> 24:41.520
I made inquiries.

24:41.640 --> 24:42.840
But the homeowners
had made a complaint.

24:42.960 --> 24:44.840
How could they when
they've been deported?

24:44.960 --> 24:46.760
It's not my job to
save the world, Ted.

24:46.880 --> 24:47.680
I'll leave that to you.

24:58.560 --> 24:59.920
What did he want?

25:00.040 --> 25:01.440
Wanted to know what wewere doing in South Auckland

25:01.560 --> 25:03.640
in the middle of the night.

25:03.760 --> 25:05.440
I told him it wasn't
the middle of the night.

25:05.560 --> 25:06.600
It was closer to the morning.

25:09.880 --> 25:10.800
Was that a wrong thing to say?

25:10.920 --> 25:11.720
No, no.

25:11.840 --> 25:13.080
It's good, Phineas.

25:13.200 --> 25:14.400
If he asks again,
just tell him we were

25:14.520 --> 25:16.880
passing through, going fishing.

25:17.000 --> 25:18.040
Yeah, that would've been good.

25:21.440 --> 25:22.240
How are you going?

25:22.360 --> 25:25.840
Well, it's a bit tough.

25:25.960 --> 25:28.480
Carol used to bring
in the housekeeping.

25:28.600 --> 25:30.320
She'd go on at me about
not pulling my weight.

25:30.440 --> 25:33.880
Look, we do that payroll joband we're right back on track.

25:34.000 --> 25:36.400
And you know, Carol--

25:36.520 --> 25:38.480
she misses you.

25:38.600 --> 25:40.840
She said she never
wanted to see me again.

25:40.960 --> 25:45.680
She was up all nightcrying something terrible.

25:45.800 --> 25:48.600
Ah, she drives me crazythe way she goes on at me.

25:48.720 --> 25:50.120
Maybe we're better off apart.

25:50.240 --> 25:52.960
Women-- they're
not the same as us.

25:53.080 --> 25:54.760
Half the time, they're
awash with hormones.

25:54.880 --> 25:57.960
It's no wonder they speak awhole lot of crazy rubbish.

25:58.080 --> 25:59.360
There's that effect.

25:59.480 --> 26:01.440
You got to make
allowances for them--

26:01.560 --> 26:03.360
treat them kind.

26:03.480 --> 26:04.640
It's a lot like
dealing with horses.

26:07.520 --> 26:09.480
[inaudible].

26:09.600 --> 26:11.640
But Mamie's offered
to stay on and cook.

26:11.760 --> 26:12.680
Is that what you want?

26:12.800 --> 26:15.840
At your age?

26:15.960 --> 26:17.440
I'll tell you what.

26:17.560 --> 26:20.280
Shout your mum a trip to seeyour sister in [inaudible]..

26:20.400 --> 26:21.720
Come over to the
house and see Carol

26:21.840 --> 26:23.560
and tell her how you feel.

26:23.680 --> 26:26.080
